inertia /ɪnˈɜːʃə/

1. N-UNCOUNT If you have a feeling of inertia , you feel very lazy and unwilling to move or be active. 懒惰 

例： He resented her inertia, her lack of energy and self-direction. 他讨厌她的懒惰、缺乏活力和自我。 

2. N-UNCOUNT Inertia is the tendency of a physical object to remain still or to continue moving, unless a force is applied to it. 惯性 [技术]

</div>

